description:
Cross-file bug: lichen_peer_add() and lichen_peer_remove() acquire rx_mutex (lines 379, 425) without checking lichen_lora_l2_needs_reinit() first.

If the lora_l2 RX thread was forcibly aborted while holding rx_mutex (during lichen_l2_input() callback processing), the mutex is left locked. Any subsequent call to lichen_peer_add() or lichen_peer_remove() will deadlock forever on k_mutex_lock(&rx_mutex, K_FOREVER).

Compare to lichen_l2_enable() which checks needs_reinit() BEFORE acquiring any mutex (line 627).

Sequence:
1. RX thread receives packet, calls callback -> lichen_l2_input()
2. lichen_l2_input() acquires rx_mutex (line 994)
3. User calls lichen_lora_l2_stop()
4. stop() waits for thread, times out, calls k_thread_abort()
5. Thread is killed while holding rx_mutex
6. aborted flag is set (lora_l2.c:454)
7. stop() returns
8. Application calls lichen_peer_add() - DEADLOCKS on rx_mutex (line 379)

Fix: Add needs_reinit() check at the start of lichen_peer_add() and lichen_peer_remove():

int lichen_peer_add(...) {
    if (lichen_lora_l2_needs_reinit()) {
        LOG_ERR("Peer add rejected: LoRa L2 requires re-initialization");
        return -ECANCELED;
    }
    k_mutex_lock(&rx_mutex, K_FOREVER);
    ...
}
